Pathogene-on-FHIR: Making Pathogen Genome Data Interoperable with Patient Health Records
========================================================================================

This presentation is scheduled for the:

* ISMB 2026 Technology Track presentation


Overview
--------

The integration of clinical data with pathogen genomic data offers unprecedented opportunities for tracking infectious diseases, predicting clinical outcomes, and managing antimicrobial resistance (AMR). However, digital health researchers face severe bottlenecks due to non availability of integrated data representations. To bridge this gap, we present **Pathogene-on-FHIR**, an ecosystem designed to harmonise the ingestion of clinical records and pathogen genomic data. By mapping heterogeneous datasets to standard HL7 FHIR (Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources) schemas, the platform ensures that patient Electronic Health Record (EHR) data and pathogen genomic information is seamlessly harmonised, and immediately ready for downstream machine learning modeling of infectious diseases.


