   Yashpal is a Postdoctoral Research Fellow at the Central Clinical School, Monash University.


Key Takeaways
--------------

#. Understanding the core architecture of the Pathogene-on-FHIR utility
#. Ingesting raw clinical records and pathogen metadata into FHIR framework
#. Extracting machine learning ready datamatrix from the integrated data


Prerequisites
-------------

Our target audience is clinical data scientists, and health informatics developers. For conceptual understanding of the framework, no prior knowledge of HL7 FHIR is required. To explore the codebase or pipeline deployment, attendees are recommended to have a prior knowledge of Python and containerised workflows.


Technical Dependencies
----------------------

#. Python 3.10 or above
#. Docker/Apptainer
#. PostgreSQL DB
#. HAPI-FHIR


